          %br
        %h2 prayer
        %p  
          Here are som resources for prayer.
        %h2 kids
        %p
          We want to make sure our children can remain engaged! A range of colouring and activity funsheets and other suggested resources are being sent out to parents each week - and we have created a new private 
          %a{:href => 'https://www.facebook.com/groups/winchestervineyardkids/'} facebook page 
          for parents to connect. We will be sharing fun interactive activities for you and your kids to get involved with - see the email from Louise for all details.
        %h2 points of connection
        %p  
          For points of connection, such as Thought for the day with Paul, worship with Nigel, Zoom prayer gatherings, Life Groups, and Youth gatherings, please visit our Keep Connected page: 
          %a{:href => 'https://www.winvin.org.uk/keepconnected/'} here.
          %br
        %h2 have you got stories
        %p 
          We love to hear your stories! Have you been inspired into action through a sermon series? Stepped out of your comfort zone to be Jesus in your community? Maybe you've been healed? Has God's love and peace filled you when you've needed it most? God is doing amazing things all the time and we would LOVE to hear about it. Please email your stories and pictures to us at
          %a{:href => 'mailto:stories@winvin.org.uk'} stories@winvin.org.uk
        %h2 office
        %p 
          The office team will be checking phone messages and emails regularly. If you have an urgent request, the best way to contact us is via email. 
          %br
          To contact us please email hello@winvin.org.uk or call 01962 863217.
